 Sure, I can help you create an XML mission plan based on your requirements. Here's an example of what the XML file might look like:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mission>
    <name>Temperature and CO2 Sampling Mission</name>
    <description>A mission to collect temperature and CO2 readings from trees in the orchard.</description>
    <steps>
        <step id="1">
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
            <condition>If the picture shows low temperature</condition>
            <next>
                <action>Take a temperature reading</action>
                <condition>If the reading is also low</condition>
                <next>
                    <action>Take a CO2 sample</action>
                    <condition>If the reading is also low</condition>
                    <next>
                        <action>Drive to a far away tree and repeat the process</action>
                    </next>
                </next>
            </next>
        </step>
        <step id="2">
            <action>Drive to end</action>
        </step>
    </steps>
</mission>
```
This XML file defines a mission with two steps. The first step involves taking a picture of the tree, checking if the temperature in the picture is low, and if it is, taking a temperature reading. If the temperature reading is also low, the robot will take a CO2 sample. If both the temperature and CO2 readings are low, the robot will drive to a far away tree and repeat the process. If any of these conditions are not met, the robot will move on to the second step, which involves driving to the end of the mission.

I hope this helps you get started with creating your XML mission plan! Let me know if you have any questions or need further assistance. 